ing resources. &#10;The goal should not be to EXclude students from utilizing public school services or programs. The goal should be to INclude all who wish to participate, and therefore to fix problems with the funding system so that all students are supported to the extent that they wish to participate. If my state could figure out how to do this and make it win-win for everyone, I don't see why other states can't figure it out as well. (In fact, my state has figured it out so well that districts actually advertise their programs to homeschooled students, because they WANT them to come, sign up for even just one class or sport, so that they can get that funding!) "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="977" language="en" documentId="656" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="KRAMV" date="09/06/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=37" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="656" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="322"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="323" end="977"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>